\section{Summary}




The stopping position measurements have better linearity and accuracy (2.2-1.2\%) than the energy measurements (5.5\% to 3.5\%), confirmed by simulations,
and thus are expected to provide more accurate WEPL calibration for the image reconstruction.  The behavior of range stack detector is well modelled by GEANT,
with a few dicrepancies in energy deposition at low energy and energy resolution.


